HEADWORD: Macrograph
<hw>Mac"ro*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Macro-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>A picture of an
object as seen by the naked eye (that is, unmagnified); <as>as, a
<ex>macrograph</ex> of a metallic fracture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Macrography</ent>⟦br⟧
